bar
------------------------------------------
lemonbar (formerly known as bar) is a lightweight statusbar based on XCB.
Provides full UTF-8 support, basic formatting, RandR and Xinerama support and
EWMH compliance without wasting your precious memory.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.203.gf78009cb1ccf
  libxcb-randr0-1.17.0-1
  libxcb1-1.17.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libxcb-devel-1.17.0-1
  libxcb-randr-devel-1.17.0-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  perl-5.36.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/LemonBoy/bar

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/LemonBoy/bar/archive/refs/tags/v1.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bar-1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bar-1.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bar-1.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bar-1.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bar)
  /usr/bin/lemonbar.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bar.README
  /usr/share/doc/bar/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/bar/README.pod
  /usr/share/man/man1/lemonbar.1.gz

